        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2025-06-08 15:59:14.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2025-06-08 17:33:07.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-0000 llite: improve ACTIVE_WRITER lock handling",
        "message": "LU-0000 llite: improve ACTIVE_WRITER lock handling\n\nThis patch improves ACTIVE_WRITER lock handling for immediate\nmirror files with three key changes:\n\n1. Change ACTIVE_WRITER locks from LCK_EX to LCK_CW mode to\n   enable concurrent write access, which is appropriate for\n   immediate mirror scenarios where multiple writers can\n   coexist.\n\n2. Use ldlm_lock_decref_and_cancel() instead of\n   ldlm_lock_decref() to ensure locks are properly cancelled\n   and send cancellation RPCs to the server, allowing the\n   server-side active writer count to be decremented.\n\n3. Add enhanced debug logging to track blocking AST\n   assignment for better debugging of lock lifecycle.\n\nThese changes ensure proper lock cancellation and server-side\ncounter management for ACTIVE_WRITER locks.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I70f619a2d65c5cb898d6763f7acc522aa781557a\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
